==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Khan
<hw>Khan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pers. & Tart.
<ets>kh</ets>⟦amac⟧<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <altsp>[Also <asp>kan</asp>,
<asp>kaun</asp>.]</altsp> <def>A king; a prince; a chief; a governor; --
so called among the Tartars, Turks, and Persians, and in countries now
or formerly governed by them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Khan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Khan
<hw>Khan</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per. <ets>kh⟦amac⟧n</ets>,
<ets>kh⟦amac⟧nah</ets>, house, tent, inn.]</ety> <def>An Eastern inn or
caravansary.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>kawn</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Khanate</ent>⟦br⟧
